This is the level you should write at:

Project: DSA Notes Navigator (Personal Project)

Wrong (junior):

Built a markdown viewer using Next.js and React.

Implemented sidebar navigation and search.

Correct (your level):

Designed and built a production-grade learning platform with deterministic SPA navigation, supporting split-view, revision mode, and keyboard-first UX.

Implemented a token-based access control system with Redis-backed quota enforcement and session locking to prevent API abuse and credential sharing.

Built a backend gating layer for all GitHub API calls, ensuring pre-check quota validation and post-success consumption semantics.

Designed an admin control plane to manage tokens, quotas, session scopes, and trigger cache revalidation.

Architected a single-scroll-container SPA with zero route remounts and shared state across split panes.

Implemented TOC synchronization and active section tracking using custom markdown parsing.

Ensured no duplicate backend fetches across split views via centralized state and request deduplication.

These bullets scream: “this person thinks in systems”.

